{"questionId":"12807","questionHtml":"<p>In an arithmetic sequence, the sum of the 3rd and 8th terms is 1.</p>\n<p>Given that the sum of the first seven terms is 35, determine the first term and the common&nbsp;difference.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>attempting to form two equations involving&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {{u_1} + 2d} \\right) + \\left( {{u_1} + 7d} \\right) = 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{7}{2}\\left[ {2{u_1} + 6d} \\right] = 35\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>[</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>]</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>35</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{u_1} + 9d = 1\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"14{u_1} + 42d = 70\\,\\,\\,\\left( {2{u_1} + 6d = 10} \\right)\">\n  <mn>14</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>42</mn>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>70</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for any two correct equations</p>\n<p>attempting to solve their equations:<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1} = 14\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>14</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d =&nbsp; - 3\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12807","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ2.H_1","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"In an arithmetic sequence, the sum of the 3rd and 8th terms is 1. Given that the sum of the first seven terms is 35, determine the first term and the common difference.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"H_1","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}